0.2 Function to produce graphs

#seurat object = seurat object subsetted to only include clusters of interest, ex all pallium clusters
#treatment = 'age'
#cluster_idents = 'clusterInterp2' from seurat object
#samples = 'batch' 
#order_facets = clusters of interest, ex all pallium clusters
#subset_graph = clusters to put on facet graph, ex select pallium clusters
#order = order of ages (6dpf, 15dpf, adult)
#order_batches = order of batches to graph (6dpf_b0, 6dpf_b1...)


calculate_cluster_composition <- function(seurat.obj, treatment = NULL, cluster_idents = NULL, samples = NULL, order = NULL, order_facets = NULL, dataset = NULL, order_batches = NULL, subset_graph = NULL){
  library(ggplot2)
  library(tibble)
  library(rstatix)
  library(ggpubr)
  clusters <- as.data.frame(seurat.obj[[cluster_idents]]) #makes clusters into dataframe
  treatments <- as.data.frame(seurat.obj[[treatment]]) #makes age into dataframe
  animals <- as.data.frame(seurat.obj[[samples]]) #makes batch into dataframe
  
  df<- cbind(clusters, treatments, animals) #puts clusters, age, and batch into dataframe
  colnames(df) <- c("clusters", "Treatment", "animals") #renames columns
  
  count <- table(df$clusters, df$animals) #makes table with counts of each cluster in each batch
  pct <- sweep(count, 2, colSums(count), "/")*100 #makes table with percent cells in each cluster, per batch
  
  df1 <- df[!duplicated(df$animals), ] #makes df with one of each batch
  rownames(df1) <- df1$animals #makes rownames batch names
  df1$clusters <- NULL #gets rid of cluster column
  
  df1 <- df1 %>% tidyr::drop_na()
  
  df2 <- data.frame(pct) #turns pct into dataframe
  colnames(df2) <- c('clusters', 'animals', 'Percent') #renames columns
  df3 <- merge(df2, df1, by = 'animals') #makes dataframe with batch, clusters, percent, and age
  df2$clusters <- factor(df2$clusters, levels = c(order_facets)) #change order of clusters
  df2$animals <- factor(df2$animals, levels = c(order_batches)) #change order of batches
  df2 <- df2 %>% tidyr::drop_na()

  p0 <- ggplot(df2, aes(fill=clusters, y=Percent, x=animals)) + #plot proportion bargraph
    geom_bar(position="fill", stat="identity") +
    scale_fill_manual(values=cols) +
    theme_classic() +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1)) +
    xlab("")
  
  df3$Treatment <- factor(df3$Treatment, levels = order) #puts ages in order
  df3$clusters <- factor(df3$clusters, levels = order_facets) #puts clusters in order
  df3 <- df3 %>% tidyr::drop_na()
  clusters <- factor(clusters)
  
  stat.test <- df3 %>% #multiple t tests
  group_by(clusters) %>%
  t_test(Percent ~ Treatment) %>%
  adjust_pvalue(method = "BH") %>%
  add_significance()
  
  stat.test <- stat.test %>% add_xy_position(x = "Treatment") #add positions for pvalue label
  stat.testfiltered <- filter(stat.test, clusters %in% subset_graph) #subset p-values to include only those on graphs
  
   My_Theme = theme(
    axis.title.x = element_blank(),
    axis.text.x = element_blank(),
    axis.title.y = element_text(size = 15),
    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 20),
    axis.title=element_text(size = 25),
    legend.text = element_text(size = 18),
    legend.position = 'bottom' ,
    plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5, size = 14),
    strip.text =  element_text(size = 10)
  )
  #strip.text.x = element_text(size = 20), axis.text.y=element_text(size=20), axis.title=element_text(size = 25)
  

  p <- ggplot(subset(df3, clusters %in% subset_graph), aes(Treatment, Percent, color = Treatment, fill = Treatment)) +
    geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.8) +
    scale_fill_manual(values=c("#f8d629", "#55c4cc", "#cf76d4")) +
    geom_point(pch = 1, position = position_jitterdodge()) +
    scale_color_manual(values=c("#f8d629", "#55c4cc", "#cf76d4")) +
    theme_bw() + 
    facet_grid(.~clusters, 
               labeller = labeller(clusters = label_wrap_gen(10))) +
    My_Theme +
    theme(legend.title=element_blank()) +
    stat_pvalue_manual(inherit.aes = FALSE, stat.testfiltered, label = "p.adj.signif")
  df4 <- tidyr::pivot_wider(df3[,1:3], names_from = animals, values_from= Percent) #make untidy table to export 
  
  return(list(p0, p, stat.test, df3, df4))
}


#1 is cell composition stacked bar plot
#2 is box plot
#3 is p-values
#4 is dataframe with age, batch, and cluster
#5 is untidy data for exporting

0.3 All clusters

#set order of clusters
order_facets <- c("dHabenula", "vHabenula", "Microglia", "OPC", "Oligodendrocytes", "Olf. Bulb", "Progenitor 02", "Progenitor 01", "Nk-like", "Epithelial/Endothelial Cells", "Cycling progenitors 01", "Cycling progenitors 02", "Comm. Pa Precursors", "Comm. SPa Precursors", "Pallium IN01", "Pallium IN02", "Subpallium IN", "Subpallium 03",  "Pallium 01", "Pallium 02", "Pallium 03", "Pallium 04", "Pallium 05", "Pallium 06", "Pallium 07", "Pallium 08", "Pallium 09", "Subpallium 01", "Subpallium 02", "PoA 02", "Subpallium 04", "Subpallium 05", "Subpallium 06", "Subpallium 07", "Subpallium 08", "PoA 01", "Astrocyte-like", "Pallium IN03")

#run function with all clusters
allclusters <- calculate_cluster_composition(seurat.obj = forebrain.integrated, treatment = 'age', cluster_idents = 'clusterInterp2', samples = 'batch', order_facets = order_facets, order = order, order_batches = order_batches, subset_graph = order_facets)

#list of all pallium clusters
